title: OfficialArchicadApiMasterModels
description: A consolidated, single-file schema for the official Archicad JSON API.

projectMapNavigatorItemId.description: The ID of the navigator item to be cloned. Only navigator items from the project map can be cloned.

parentNavigatorItemId.description: The ID of the navigator item below which the new view will be inserted. Only navigator items from the view map are allowed.

createdNavigatorItemId.description: The ID of the new navigator item in view map.
The ID of the new layout navigator item in the layout book.

createdSubsetId.description: The ID of the new subset navigator item in the layout book.

folderParameters.description: This is the name of the new folder.

parentNavigatorItemId.description: The newly created folder will be placed under this parent item. If this parameter is not given the folder will be created as the first item in the View Map list.

previousNavigatorItemId.description: The newly created folder will be placed after this sibling item. If this parameter is not given the folder will be created as the first item under the parent.

modelViewPenTableId.description: Model view pen table identifier or an error.

layoutBookPenTableId.description: Layout book pen table identifier or an error.

elementClassifications.description: The list of element classification item identifiers. Order of the ids are the same as in the input. Non-existing elements or non-existing classification systems are represented by error objects.

elementTypes.description: If this parameter is given, then only related elements with the requested types will be listed.

version.description: The version of the running Archicad.

buildNumber.description: The build number of the running Archicad.

languageCode.description: The language code of the running Archicad.

imageWidth.description: The width of the preview image.

imageHeight.description: The height of the preview image.

backgroundColor.description: The background color of the preview image.

previewImages.description: The preview images of the profiles.

properties.description: List of property names whose ids are requested.

List of the ids of the requested properties. Order of the ids are the same as in the input. Existing properties are represented by propertyId objects, non-existing properties are represented by error objects.

propertyValuesForElementComponents.description: List of property value lists. The order of the outer list is that of the given components. The order of the inner lists are that of the given properties.

propertyValuesForElements.description: List of property value lists. The order of the outer list is that of the given elements. The order of the inner lists are that of the given properties.

publisherSetNames.description: The names of available publisher sets.

onlyEditable.description: Optional parameter that defines whether the selection list should include only the editable elements or all of them. The default value is FALSE

onlySupportedTypes.description: Optional parameter. When it is set to true, only elements with types that are supported by any other JSON API command will be returned.

available.description: Returns true if the command is available.

isAlive.description: Returns true if the connection is alive.

newName.description: New name of the navigator item.

newId.description: New ID of the navigator item.

newName.description: New name of the navigator item.

newId.description: New ID of the navigator item.

AddOnCommandId.description: The identifier of an Add-On command.

commandNamespace.description: The namespace of the Add-On command.

commandName.description: The name of the Add-On command.

AddOnCommandIds.description: A list of Add-On command identifiers.

AddOnCommandParameters.description: The input parameters of an Add-On command.

AddOnCommandResponse.description: The response returned by an Add-On command.

AttributeFolderId.description: The identifier of an attribute folder.

AttributeFolderIds.description: A list of attribute folder identifiers.

AttributeIdOrError.description: The attribute's identifier or an error.

AttributeIndexAndGuid.description: The complete identifier of an attribute.

AttributeIndexAndGuidOrError.description: The attribute's identifier or an error.

AttributeIndicesAndGuids.description: A list of complete attribute identifiers.

AttributeFolderName.description: The name of an attribute folder. Legal names are not empty, and do not begin or end with whitespace.

AttributeFolderPath.description: A list of attribute folder names. May be empty.

AttributeFolder.description: Identifies an attribute folder. The path of the root folder is repesented by empty array.

AttributeFolderOrError.description: An attribute folder or an error.

AttributeFolderCreationParameters.description: Used to create an attribute folder. The folder type and it's path needs to be provided.

AttributeFolderRenameParameters.description: Used to rename an attribute folder. The folder is identified by it's Id.

AttributeFolderStructures.description: A list of attribute folder structures.

AttributeFolderStructure.description: The details of an attribute folder structure.

attributes.description: The names and identifiers of the attributes contained in this folder.

subfolders.description: The subfolders of this attribute folder.

AttributeFolderStructureOrError.description: An attribute folder structure or an error.

AttributeHeader.description: The header object of an attribute.

AppearanceType.description: The appearance type of a line or fill attribute.

PenIndex.description: The index number of a pen.

PenTableAttributeOrError.description: A pen table attribute or an error.

PenTableAttributes.description: A list of pen table attributes and potential errors.

isLocked.description: Defines whether the layer is locked or not.

isHidden.description: Defines whether the layer is hidden or not.

isWireframe.description: Defines whether the elements placed on this layer are visible as wireframes or a solid model.

LayerAttributeOrError.description: A layer attribute or an error.

LayerAttributes.description: A list of layer attributes and potential errors.

FillPattern.description: The pattern of the fill attribute, stored in a 64 bit unsigned integer, and represented as an 8x8 matrix. Each byte in the value is a row, and the bits are the columns of the matrix.

FillTypeId.description: The filling type of a fill attribute.

FillAttributeOrError.description: A fill attribute or an error.

FillAttributes.description: A list of fill attributes and potential errors.

MaterialTypeId.description: The material type of a surface attribute.

ambientReflection.description: The ambient reflection of the surface attribute.

diffuseReflection.description: The diffuse reflection of the surface attribute.

specularReflection.description: The specular reflection of the surface attribute.

transparencyAttenuation.description: The transparency attenuation of the surface attribute.

emissionAttenuation.description: The emission attenuation of the surface attribute.

surfaceColor.description: The surface color of the surface attribute.

specularColor.description: The specular color of the surface attribute.

emissionColor.description: The emission color of the surface attribute.

fillId.description: The identifier of the surface attribute's fill component.

transparency.description: The transparency of the surface attribute.

shine.description: The shininess of the surface attribute.

texture.description: The texture of the surface attribute.

SurfaceAttributeOrError.description: A surface attribute or an error.

SurfaceAttributes.description: A list of surface attributes and potential errors.

name.description: The name of the modifier.

useWith.description: The list of element types for which this profile is available.

width.description: The default width (horizontal size) of the profile.

height.description: The default height (vertical size) of the profile.

minimumWidth.description: The minimum width (horizontal size) of the profile.

minimumHeight.description: The minimum height (vertical size) of the profile.

widthStretchable.description: Defines whether the profile's width can be increased beyond its default value or not.

heightStretchable.description: Defines whether the profile's height can be increased beyond its default value or not.

hasCoreSkin.description: Defines whether the profile has a core skin or not.

ProfileAttributeOrError.description: A profile attribute or an error.

ProfileAttributes.description: A list of the profile attributes and potential errors.

CompositeLine.description: A contour or separator line component for a composite attribute.

linePenIndex.description: The index of the line pen.

CompositeLineList.description: A list of contour/separator lines for the composite.

CompositeSkin.description: A skin component for a composite attribute.

framePenIndex.description: The index of the frame pen.

thickness.description: The thickness of the composite skin.

isCore.description: Defines whether the composite skin is part of the core or not.

isFinish.description: Defines whether the composite skin is part of the finish or not.

totalThickness.description: The total thickness of the composite.

compositeSkins.description: The skins of the composite attribute.

compositeLines.description: The contour and separator lines of the composite attribute.

useWith.description: The list of element types for which this composite is available.

CompositeAttributeOrError.description: A composite attribute or an error.

CompositeAttributes.description: A list of the composite attributes and potential errors.

weight.description: The thickness of the pen defined in millimeters.

Pens.description: A collection of pens in a pen table.

name.description: The name of the texture.

LineType.description: The type of a line attribute.

LineItemType.description: The type of a line item.

centerOffset.description: The vertical distance from the origin of the symbol line. Used in separator, center dot, and centerline item types.

length.description: The length of the item. Used in centerline, right angle, and parallel item types.

begPosition.description: The beginning position of the item. Used in dot, right angle, parallel, line, circle, and arc item types.

endPosition.description: The end position of the item. Used in line item type.

radius.description: The radius of the item. Used in circle and arc item types.

begAngle.description: The beginning angle of the item, measured from the vertical axis. Used in the arc item type.

endAngle.description: The ending angle of the item, measured from the vertical axis. Used in the arc item type.

LineItems.description: A list of dash or line items.

displayScale.description: The original scale of the line.

period.description: The length of the dashed or symbol line's period.

height.description: The height of the symbol line.

LineAttributeOrError.description: A line attribute or an error.

LineAttributes.description: A list of line attributes and potential errors.

categoryCode.description: The category code of the zone.

stampName.description: The stamp name of the zone category.

stampMainGuid.description: The main part of the stamp library part's unique identifier.

stampRevisionGuid.description: The revision part of the stamp library part's unique identifier.

ZoneCategoryAttributeOrError.description: A zone category attribute or an error.

ZoneCategoryAttributes.description: A list of zone category attributes and potential errors.

id.description: The id of the building material.

connectionPriority.description: The connection priority of the building material.

cutFillId.description: The identifier of the building material attribute's fill component.

cutFillPenIndex.description: The cut fill pen index of the building material.

cutSurfaceId.description: The identifier of the building material attribute's surface component.

BuildingMaterialAttributeOrError.description: A building material attribute or an error.

BuildingMaterialAttributes.description: A list of building material attributes and potential errors.

LayerCombinationAttributes.description: A list of layer combination attributes and potential errors.

layerAttributeIds.description: The list of identifiers belonging to the layer attributes referenced in this layer combination.

LayerCombinationAttributeOrError.description: A layer combination attribute or an error.

ClassificationItemAvailability.description: Contains the ids of property definitions available for the given classification item.

ClassificationItemAvailabilityOrError.description: Contains the ids of property definitions available for the given classification item or error.

ClassificationItemAvailabilityList.description: A list of classification item avalabilities.

PropertyDefinitionAvailabilityOrError.description: Contains the ids of classification items the given property definiton is available for or error.

PropertyDefinitionAvailabilityList.description: A list of classification item avalabilities.

ClassificationSystemId.description: The identifier of a classification system.

ClassificationSystemIds.description: A list of classification system identifiers.

ClassificationItemId.description: The identifier of a classification item.

ClassificationItemIds.description: A list of classification item identifiers.

ClassificationIdOrError.description: A classification identifier or an error.

ClassificationIdsOrErrors.description: A list of element classification identifiers or errors.

ElementClassifications.description: A list of element classification identifiers.

ElementClassificationsOrErrors.description: A list of element classification identifiers or errors.

ClassificationItemsOrErrors.description: A list of classification items or errors.

ClassificationItemDetails.description: The details of a classification item.

name.description: The display name of the classification item.

name.description: The display name of the classification system.

date.description: The release date of the classification system's current version.

UserDefinedPropertyUserId.description: The unique identifier of a User-Defined Property, identified by its name.

localizedName.description: A two-element list of the localized name parts. The first element is the name of the group the property belongs to, and the second element is the actual name of the property.

BuiltInPropertyUserId.description: The unique identifier of a Built-In Property, identified by its name.

nonLocalizedName.description: The non-localized name of the Built-In Property.

PropertyUserId.description: The unique identifier of a Property, identified by its name. May represent a User-Defined or a Built-In Property.

PropertyType.description: The type of a property group or a property definition.

PropertyGroupId.description: The identifier of a property group.

PropertyGroupIds.description: A list of property group identifiers.

PropertyIdOrError.description: A property identifier or an error.

PropertyIdsOrErrors.description: A list of property identifiers or errors.

name.description: The property group name.

PropertyBasicDefaultValue.description: Default value of the property in case of a basic property value (ie. not an expression).

PropertyGroupOrError.description: A property group or an error.

PropertyGroupsOrErrors.description: A list of property groups or errors.

PropertyDefinition.description: A property definition. The default value of a property appears if and only if it is a custom property and is not an expression type property. (This may change in the future.)

name.description: The localized name of the property.

isEditable.description: Defines whether the property is editable or not.

type.description: Defines the type of the property's value.

possibleEnumValues.description: The possible enum values of the property when the property type is enumeration.

PropertyDefinitionOrError.description: A property definition or an error.

PropertyDefinitionsOrErrors.description: A list of property definitions or errors.

NormalNumberPropertyValue.description: A number property value containing a valid numeric value.

NormalIntegerPropertyValue.description: An integer property value containing a valid integer number.

NormalStringPropertyValue.description: A string property value containing a valid string.

NormalBooleanPropertyValue.description: A boolean property value containing a valid boolean value.

NormalLengthPropertyValue.description: A length property value containing a real length value. The value is measured in SI (meters).

NormalAreaPropertyValue.description: An area property value containing a real area. The value is measured in SI (square meters).

NormalVolumePropertyValue.description: A volume property value containing a real volume. The value is measured in SI (cubic meters).

NormalAnglePropertyValue.description: An angle property value containing a real angle. The value is measured in SI (radians).

NormalNumberListPropertyValue.description: A number list property value containing numbers in an array.

NormalIntegerListPropertyValue.description: An integer list property value containing integers in an array.

NormalStringListPropertyValue.description: A string list property value containing strings in an array.

NormalBooleanListPropertyValue.description: A boolean list property value containing boolean values in an array.

NormalLengthListPropertyValue.description: A length list property value containing length values in an array. The values are measured in SI (meters).

NormalAreaListPropertyValue.description: An area list property value containing areas in an array. The values are measured in SI (square meters).

NormalVolumeListPropertyValue.description: A volume list property value containing volumes in an array. The values are measured in SI (cubic meters).

NormalAngleListPropertyValue.description: An angle list property value containing angles in an array. The values are measured in SI (radians).

NormalSingleEnumPropertyValue.description: A single enumeration property value containing the ID of the selected enum value.

NormalMultiEnumPropertyValue.description: A multiple choice enumeration property value containing the IDs of the selected enum values in an array.

UserUndefinedPropertyValue.description: A userUndefined value means that there is no actual number/string/etc. value, but the user deliberately set an Undefined value: this is a valid value, too.

NotAvailablePropertyValue.description: A notAvailable value means that the property is not available for the property owner (and therefore it has no property value for it).

NotEvaluatedPropertyValue.description: A notEvaluated value means that the property could not be evaluated for the property owner for some reason.

NormalOrUserUndefinedPropertyValue.description: A normal or a userUndefined property value.

PropertyValue.description: A normal, userUndefined, notAvailable or notEvaluated property value.

DisplayValueEnumId.description: An enumeration value identifier using the displayed value.

NonLocalizedValueEnumId.description: An enumeration value identifier using the nonlocalized value.

EnumValueId.description: The identifier of a property enumeration value.

PossibleEnumValue.description: The description of an enumeration value.

nonLocalizedValue.description: Nonlocalized value of the enumeration if there is one.

PropertyValueOrErrorItem.description: A property value or an error

PropertyValuesOrError.description: A list of property values or an error.

PropertyValuesOrErrorArray.description: A list of property value lists.

ElementPropertyValue.description: A property value with the identifiers of the property and its owner element.

ElementPropertyValues.description: A list of element property values.

PropertyIdsOfElement.description: A list property identifiers of an owner element.

PropertyIdsOfElementOrError.description: A list property identifiers of an owner element or an error.

PropertyIdsOfElementOrErrorArray.description: A list of property identifiers of elements or errors.

SuccessfulExecutionResult.description: The result of a successful execution.

FailedExecutionResult.description: The result of a failed execution.

error.description: The details of an execution failure.

Guid.description: A Globally Unique Identifier (or Universally Unique Identifier) in its string representation as defined in RFC 4122.

Date.description: A date in its string representation as defined in ISO 8601: YYYY-MM-DD.

TypeOfElement.description: An element id and its corresponding element type.

TypeOfElementOrError.description: The type of an element or an error.

TypeOfElementOrErrorList.description: A list of element types or errors.

ElementsWrapper.description: A wrapper for a list of elements.

ElementsOrError.description: A list of elements or an error.

Image.description: An image encoded as a Base64 string.

content.description: The image content as a string .

Images.description: A list of images and potential errors.

name.description: The name of the folder.

BoundingBox2D.description: The 2D bounding box of an element.

xMin.description: The minimum X value of the bounding box.

yMin.description: The minimum Y value of the bounding box.

xMax.description: The maximum X value of the bounding box.

yMax.description: The maximum Y value of the bounding box.

BoundingBox2DOrError.description: A 2D bounding box or an error.

BoundingBox3D.description: A 3D bounding box of an element.

xMin.description: The minimum X value of the bounding box.

yMin.description: The minimum Y value of the bounding box.

zMin.description: The minimum Z value of the bounding box.

xMax.description: The maximum X value of the bounding box.

yMax.description: The maximum Y value of the bounding box.

zMax.description: The maximum Z value of the bounding box.

BoundingBox3DOrError.description: A 3D bounding box or an error.

RGBColor.description: A color model represented via its red, green and blue components.

red.description: The red component of the color model.

green.description: The green component of the color model.

blue.description: The blue component of the color model.

Subset.description: A set of options used to assign IDs to the layouts contained in the subset.

name.description: The name for the layout subset.

includeToIDSequence.description: Defines whether this subset is included in automatic ID assignment or not.

customNumbering.description: Defines whether the IDs are generated automatically or a custom numbering is used.

continueNumbering.description: Defines whether to continue using the ID assignment of the upper levels or not. If 'true', layouts within this subset are going to be assigned IDs as if they were not within this subset, but part of the level above. In this case you only use the Subset as a logical grouping which has no effect on IDs.

useUpperPrefix.description: Defines whether to use the prefix and ID of the upper levels or not. If 'true', layouts in this subset will be assigned IDs based on the previous layout in the layout book structure.

addOwnPrefix.description: Defines whether to add own prefix to the subset or not.

numberingStyle.description: The style of the ID formatting.

startAt.description: The starting value of the numbering.

ownPrefix.description: The custom prefix for the subset.

horizontalSize.description: The horizontal size of the layout in millimeters.

verticalSize.description: The vertical size of the layout in millimeters.

leftMargin.description: The layout margin from the left side of the paper.

topMargin.description: The layout margin from the top side of the paper.

rightMargin.description: The layout margin from the right side of the paper.

bottomMargin.description: The layout margin from the bottom side of the paper.

customLayoutNumbering.description: Defines whether a unique ID is used for the current layout or not.

doNotIncludeInNumbering.description: Defines whether this layout is included in automatic ID assignment or not.

displayMasterLayoutBelow.description: Defines whether to display the master layout above or below the layout.

layoutPageNumber.description: The page number of layout when this layout contains multi-page drawings.

actPageIndex.description: The actual index of layout inside the multi-page layout.

currentRevisionId.description: The ID of the current document revision of the layout.

currentFinalRevisionId.description: The ID with optional suffix of the current document revision of the layout.

hasIssuedRevision.description: Defines whether one or more issued document revisions have already been created for the layout or not.

hasActualRevision.description: Defines whether an open document revision exists for the layout or not.

ElementComponentId.description: The identifier of an element's component.

ElementComponentIdArrayItem.description: An item of a component array.

ElementComponentsOrErrorArray.description: Array of component list or error.
